<br>
However, as I understand it, pets, unlike the warrior in my example above, are supposed to have having the exact same assist radius as far as drawing other mobs to the fight is concerned, as their owner, so in theory you don't have to worry about drawing a bunch of adds to your group by sending in a low level pet into a fight (e.g., if you are a shaman or druid with a level 30+ pet when you are level 55).<br>
<br>
So, in a nutshell, you can definitely expect a mob to target a lower level pet if they have the choice.<br>
<br>
Once you add a player into melee range, the equation changes though, so this only applies to pets meleeing mobs, not pets and players meleeing mobs.<br>
